## Phase 5: Self-Learning from Trial & Error

### [MODIFY] [agent.js](file:///c:/Users/omara/ai-assistant/src/agent.js)

After each tool execution, record the outcome:
```javascript
// In _executeTool():
const startTime = Date.now();
const result = await this._execComputerAction(input);
const elapsed = Date.now() - startTime;

// Did Claude try to click something and the screen didn't change?
// → Record: "clicking X in app Y doesn't work, suggest alternative"

// Did focus_window succeed where left_click failed?
// → Record: "for app Y, use focus_window instead of taskbar click"

// Did a keyboard shortcut work faster than a click sequence?
// → Record: "ctrl+k is faster than clicking search in Discord"
```

**Auto-learning heuristics:**
- Same action fails 2x → auto-add to failures, suggest alternative on 3rd attempt
- Same action succeeds with different params → update playbook with latest working params
- Action sequence takes >10 seconds → flag as "slow path", look for shortcuts next time

